# I think inverting the selection for Cleric based on Spontaneous casting is a better way to do this.
#    Right now, a Cleric that gains the both forms of turning/rebuking undead (from PrC or whatever)
#    Will also gain both forms of Spontaneous casting.
# At this point, it doesn't matter, since it gets converted to a single 'Spontaneous casting SA'
#  - Tir Gwaith


###Block: Spontaneous Casting abilities
# Ability Name						Category of Ability		Type				Visible	Source Page			Description of the Benefits
Spontaneous casting - Cure spells			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	SOURCEPAGE:ClassesI.rtf	BENEFIT:A good cleric (or a neutral cleric of a good deity) can channel stored spell energy into healing spells that the cleric did not prepare ahead of time. The cleric can "lose" any prepared spell that is not a domain spell in order to cast any cure spell of the same spell level or lower (a cure spell is any spell with "cure" in its name).
Spontaneous casting - Inflict spells		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	SOURCEPAGE:ClassesI.rtf	BENEFIT:An evil cleric (or a neutral cleric of an evil deity), can't convert prepared spells to cure spells but can convert them to inflict spells (an inflict spell is one with "inflict" in its name).
Spontaneous casting - Summon Nature's Ally	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	SOURCEPAGE:ClassesI.rtf	BENEFIT:A druid can channel stored spell energy into summoning spells that she hasn't prepared ahead of time. She can "lose" a prepared spell in order to cast any summon nature's ally spell of the same level or lower.

